# UI dashboard: README sync and visual regression

## Keep `ui/README.md` accurate

When you change anything that affects how contributors or agents understand the dashboard, update [`ui/README.md`](../../ui/README.md):

- Hash routes (`#/configuration`, `#/monitoring`, `#/models`, or new routes)
- Pages, shell layout, or primary user flows
- Mapping from screens to admin API endpoints or server handlers
- Designer/UX notes (app shell, sidebar, main content, patterns like tables/forms/charts/drawers)

Do not leave the README contradicting the code. For system-wide architecture, point readers to [`architecture.md`](../../architecture.md) instead of duplicating it.

## Playwright visual regression (VRT)

If the repo has Playwright screenshot tests (`test:visual` / `test:visual:update` or equivalent):

- **Intentional design or layout change:** run the documented command to update baselines (e.g. `playwright test --update-snapshots`), then commit the new baseline images in a PR that is reviewed for the visual change. Do not replace baselines by hand with arbitrary image files.
- **Accidental regression:** fix the UI or the test; do **not** update baselines to hide a real breakage.
- **Human review:** snapshot review and CI remain the source of truth; the agent does not replace that process.

If VRT is not set up yet, still avoid embedding one-off “manual” screenshots in docs as a substitute for automated baselines.
